== SCISSORS ==

Overview:

SCISSORS is a split-read aligner that maps orphaned read mates (i.e. where one 
end-mate is aligned with high mapping quality, but the other mate is unmapped), 
as well as re-maps severely clipped reads (reads mapped with many unaligned or 
“clipped-off” bases).

############
Compilation:
############

SCISSORS requires g++ and the standard C and C++ development libraries.

Enter the src directory, and type "make".

############
API Example:
############

Enter the src directory, and type "make api".
Enter the src/api directory, and type "make".

############################
Building Google C++ Testing:
############################

Just enter the src directory, and type "make test".


